        <briefdescription>
<para>This function does a minimal test on the Spi device and driver as a design example. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The purpose of this function is to illustrate the device slave functionality in polled mode. This function receives data from a master and prints the received data.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>SpiInstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the instance of Spi component.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>SpiDeviceId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the Device ID of the Spi Device and is the XPAR_&lt;SPI_instance&gt;_DEVICE_ID value from xparameters.h.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS if successful, otherwise XST_FAILURE.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function contains an infinite loop such that if the Spi device doesn&apos;t receive any data, it may never return. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
